Let {v1,v2,‚Ä¶,vk} be a set of vectors in \bbRn. Then the linear span of {v1,v2,‚Ä¶,vk} is defined asSpan‚Å¢({v1,v2,‚Ä¶,vk})=set of all possible linear combinations of¬†v1,v2,‚Ä¶,vkSpan‚Å¢({v1,v2,‚Ä¶,vk})=set of all possible linear combinations of¬†v1,v2,‚Ä¶,vk
The span of a set of vectors is every possible combination of the vectors, and any such combination is said to be in the span of the vectors.
